</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="029DC8B73E20691832CAD284FEDEFCC5" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A389B3C3E20691832CAD284FEDEFCC5" blockId="16.[151,1127,511,823]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis id="78F3472E3E20691832CAD284FE8DFD45" bold="true" box="[151,281,671,695]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Comments.</emphasis>
The specimens examined from Tangi Gharu have short, broadly conical genal processes (usually absent in 
<taxonomicName id="8D87E0BF3E2069183391D2DBFDAEFD25" authorityName="Puton" authorityYear="1876" box="[460,570,704,727]" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Bactericera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perrisii">
<emphasis id="78F3472E3E2069183391D2DBFDAEFD25" box="[460,570,704,727]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">B. perrisii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). They resemble, however, specimens from Europe and 
<collectingCountry id="3290DBAC3E2069183299D2FBFF7BFD05" box="[196,239,736,759]" name="Iraq" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Iraq</collectingCountry>
(MMBC) in other characters including the structure of the male terminalia. A variation of the shape of the genae is also known from other 
<taxonomicName id="8D87E0BF3E206918315FD31BFC14FCE5" authorityName="Puton" authorityYear="1876" box="[770,896,768,791]" class="Insecta" family="Triozidae" genus="Bactericera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="78F3472E3E206918315FD31BFC14FCE5" box="[770,896,768,791]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Bactericera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. (
<bibRefCitation id="2E16E6CD3E206918319ED2E4FEA9FCC5" author="BURCKHARDT &amp; LAUTERER" firstAuthor="BURCKHARDT" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" pagination="99 - 153" refId="ref9650" refString="BURCKHARDT D. &amp; LAUTERER P. 1997: A taxonomic reassessment of the triozid genus Bactericera (Hemiptera, Psylloidea). Journal of Natural History 31: 99 - 153." type="journal article" year="1997">BURCKHARDT &amp; LAUTERER 1997</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
